name: NutritionDiagnosisSNOMEDCT2
title: Nutrition Diagnosis SNOMED CT (2)
description: This OID was created to include one concept that could not be included in 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1095.10 due to technical issues.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: A nutrition diagnosis is used to identify and describe a specific nutrition problem identified in the nutrition status assessment that can be resolved or improved through treatment/nutrition intervention by a food and nutrition professional.),(Data Element Scope: A nutrition diagnosis (e.g. inconsistent carbohydrate intake) is different from a medical diagnosis (e.g. diabetes) but can be included in the condition, problems, concerns or nutrition status.),(Inclusion Criteria: SNOMED CT codes which document nutrition diagnoses are included.),(Exclusion Criteria: Any codes which are part of nutrition assessment, interventions, recommendations are excluded.)
